when does blaise zabini show up in which harry potter book and what page please d while his name was mentioned during the sorting ceremony in philosopher's stone blaise finally makes his first and only proper appearance in half blood prince he is one of the students invited to lunch on the hogwarts express by professor slughorn who is sizing up potential new members for his slug club after this initial meeting pansy parkinson accuses him of finding ginny weasley attractive he does not deny this outright but says that he wouldn't touch a filthy little blood traitor no matter how she looked blaise apparently passes slughorn's test as he continues to receive invitations to slughorn's parties once the school year begins he does not seem to have a high opinion of his fellow members if his comments to malfoy after the first meeting on the train are any indication in spite of this he continues to accept the invitations since the only information about blaise that existed prior to the release of half blood prince was merely his being a slytherin in harry's year his gender and nature were hotly debated by fans rowling confirmed in late that the character was male and that he would be included in future books however blaise did not appear in harry potter and the deathly hallows Hogwarts Houses Hermione Granger Ginny Weasley The Slug Club Dates in Harry Potter Minor Ravenclaws Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Draco Malfoy Magical objects in Harry Potter Hogwarts Hogwarts subjects Minor Hufflepuffs Severus Snape Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince Gryffindors in Harry Potter's year Lord Voldemort Potions in Harry Potter Weasley family Blood purity (Harry Potter) Minor characters associated with Quidditch Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone Harry Potter Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets Harry Potter (character) Albus Dumbledore James and Lily Potter J. K. Rowling Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets (video game) 